    +getName(): String
  }
  
  note top of Type
    A type is a semantic label that classifies a system based on shared
    characteristics, behaviors, or purposes. Types enable categorization and
    generalization across systems.

    **Attribute Semantics**:
    - "name": Human-readable semantic identifier for the type.

    **Consistency Rules**:
    - "name" MUST be mandatory and non-empty.
    - "name" MUST be unique among all types in the same SIE instance.
    - "name" MUST be maximum 80 characters long.
  end note

